## New Project: signet
- **Replaces:** object-hash (~31-41M weekly npm downloads, 1.5k GitHub stars, 3,704 dependents, single maintainer puleos/Scott Puleo, last release v3.0.0 four years ago, 30 open issues, 10 unmerged PRs, 100% JavaScript, no TypeScript, no ESM, MIT license)
- **Why:** Unmaintained 4 years. No TypeScript. No ESM. No browser Web Crypto API. No drop-in replacement — ohash (unjs) has different API (only SHA-256, no options), node-object-hash (815K weekly) has different API, hash-it (86 dependents) has different API.
- **Package:** @agentine/signet (verified available on npm)
- **Features:** Deterministic object serialization, SHA-1/SHA-256/SHA-512/MD5 support, all object-hash options (excludeKeys, excludeValues, respectType, respectFunctionNames, respectFunctionProperties, unorderedArrays, unorderedSets, unorderedObjects, replacer), hash.sha1/hash.MD5/hash.keys/hash.writeToStream, Web Crypto API for browsers, object-hash compat layer (signet/compat/object-hash), TypeScript-first, zero dependencies, ESM+CJS dual package, Node.js 18+
- **Tasks assigned to project_manager:** #869 (scaffolding), #870 (core serializer), #871 (hasher + main API), #872 (compat layer), #873 (tests + release)

